new perspective on youth purpose stanford center on adolescence jump to navigation s tanford c enter on a dolescence stanford university home overview people faculty and staff students visitors faculty members and affiliates activities research publications journal articles books chapters in book dissertations public presentations colloquia events conferences awards practice contact home new perspective on youth purpose new perspective on youth purpose authors kendall cotton bronk some young people demonstrate intense commitments to purposeful aims six of these young purpose exemplars were followed over a two year time period to determine how the role of purpose in their lives changed or stayed the same over time results revealed two trajectories while all of the young people were committed to the same aims over the course of the two years one cluster of youth pursued their aims using the same means as they had two years prior while another cluster had identified new means these findings suggest that purpose is likely to endure over time but that the way in which young people act on those purposes may change presented at march 8 2008 society for research on adolescence activities research publications journal articles books chapters in books dissertations other public presentations colloquia events conferences awards practice 2011 stanford center on adolescence 505 lasuen mall stanford ca 94305 3083 office 650.725 8205 fax 650.725 8207
